# Keep Docker build contexts lean by excluding large build artifacts that are
# NOT copied by any Dockerfile.
#
# IMPORTANT: do NOT exclude `dist/` — the production Dockerfile and
# Dockerfile.dev do `COPY dist/binaries/ /tmp/` (CI builds the release binaries
# there). Excluding it breaks every published image build. `rootfs/` and the
# source trees must also stay in context.
#
# Rust target dirs are the main offender (multi-GB); node_modules and VCS/log
# noise are excluded too. Dockerfile.localbuild re-runs `npm install` in its
# webapp stage, so omitting node_modules from the context is correct.
**/target/
**/node_modules/
.git/
*.log
